article.description: With one second left, Roberto Vercellino stole an inbounds pass, denying Idaho State the chance of a final basket and Northern Colorado held onto an 85-82 win on Thursday night in the Big Sky Conference.
article.headline: Vercellino, tough D late help Northern Colorado to 85-82 win
article.linkText: Vercellino, tough D late help Northern Colorado to 85-82 win
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- With one second left, Roberto Vercellino stole an inbounds pass, denying Idaho State the chance of a final basket and Northern Colorado held onto an 85-82 win on Thursday night in the Big Sky Conference. Vercellino, who played just four minutes in the second half, also blocked a potential tying shot with four seconds left. Jordan Davis led the Bears with 24 points, Andre Spight added 18. Northern Colorado (16-9, 7-5) shot 57 percent (30 of 53) and lost three players -- who scored a combined 26 points -- to fouls and two others were playing with four. There were 58 fouls and 72 free throws in the game. Neither team had a lead larger than 10 and Idaho State was trailing by eight with 1:39 to play when Brandon Boyd scored five points in a 7-1 rally that closed the gap to 83-81 in a minute. The Bengals got the ball on a turnover with 16 seconds to go, but Vercellino blocked Boyd's attempt for a layup and then had the clinching steal. Boyd scored 26 for the Bengals (10-12, 5-6), Geno Luzcando added 19.
